techmeme.title: Chinese self-driving company Pony.AI raised $413.4B in its US IPO, after pricing shares at $13, which rose 19% at open, giving it a nearly $5.4B market cap (Bailey Lipschultz/Bloomberg)
Cloudflare says it lost 55% of all logs pushed to customers over a 3.5-hour period due to a bug on November 14; Cloudflare sends ~4.5T logs to customers daily (Bill Toulas/BleepingComputer)
Foxconn Chair Young Liu says the company expects any impact of Trump's new tariffs to hit it less than its rivals, citing its global manufacturing footprint (Wen-Yee Lee/Reuters)
Raspberry Pi Compute Module 5 review: the new $45+ module is a compact Pi 5 with more power than a CM4, but whose cooling fan doesn't work with a passive cooler (Les Pounder/Tom's Hardware)
Sources: investigators suspect Chinese ship Yi Peng 3 dragged its anchor for 100+ miles to sever two Baltic internet cables, possibly at the behest of Russia (Bojan Pancevski/Wall Street Journal)
